## Installation

```bash
npm install
npm run build
```

## Start

```bash
MCP_RESOURCE_URI=urn:mcp:${serverName} \
MCP_AUTHORIZATION_SERVERS=https://auth.example.com \
MCP_JWKS_URI=https://auth.example.com/.well-known/jwks.json \
UPSTREAM_API_KEY=your_upstream_api_key \
npm start
```

By default the server listens at:

```text
http://127.0.0.1:3000/mcp
```

Use `HOST` and `PORT` to override the bind address.

## Runtime Environment

| Variable | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `HOST` | Bind host. Defaults to `127.0.0.1`. |
| `PORT` | Bind port. |
| `PUBLIC_BASE_URL` | Public server base URL used in OAuth metadata challenges. |
| `MCP_RESOURCE_URI` | Required JWT audience for this MCP server. |
| `MCP_AUTHORIZATION_SERVERS` | Comma-separated authorization server issuer URLs. |
| `MCP_JWKS_URI` | JWKS endpoint for JWT signature verification. |
| `MCP_ISSUER` | Expected token issuer. |
| `MCP_REQUIRED_SCOPES` | Comma-separated scopes required for all MCP requests. |
| `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` | Comma-separated browser origins allowed by the Origin guard. |
| `UPSTREAM_BASE_URL` | Upstream REST API base URL. |
| `UPSTREAM_API_KEY` | Separate upstream API credential for `env-credential` mode. |

## MCP Endpoints

| Endpoint | Behavior |
|---|---|
| `POST /mcp` | Authenticated MCP Streamable HTTP endpoint. |
| `GET /.well-known/oauth-protected-resource` | Public Protected Resource Metadata. |
| `GET /mcp` | Returns method not allowed. |
| `DELETE /mcp` | Returns method not allowed. |

## Security Model

The server validates every MCP request as an OAuth protected resource:

- JWT signature is verified with `MCP_JWKS_URI`.
- JWT issuer is checked with `MCP_ISSUER` or the first authorization server.
- JWT audience must equal `MCP_RESOURCE_URI`.
- Baseline scopes from `MCP_REQUIRED_SCOPES` are enforced by the SDK bearer middleware.
- Operation-level `x-mcp-scope` is enforced on `tools/call`.
- Operation-level `x-mcp-group` controls whether a tool appears in `tools/list`.
- Caller tokens are not forwarded upstream in the default `env-credential` mode.

