## Upstream Authentication

Default mode is `env-credential`, which sends `UPSTREAM_API_KEY` to the upstream API as a bearer token.

Other generated modes:

- `none` sends no upstream authorization header.
- `passthrough` forwards the caller's bearer token upstream and should only be used when that is the intended resource-server design.

